Servelets 
---------------- 
servelet is a class extending HTTPServelet 
it can able to handle client req from browser . 
generate dynamic responses (like HTML) from servers 

servelet lifecycle 
----------------------
public void init()  : initilialization (called once)

public void doGet() : Hanldes the GET request 

public void doPost() : Handles POST request 

public void destroy() : Cleaning up code (called once)


Steps for servelet application 
----------------------------------
1.install Eclipse 

2.install Apche Tomcat server 

3.Configure Tomcat in Eclipse 

4.Create Dynamic web project 

5.Create a servelet 



JAVA EE (servelet project creation )
--------------------------------------


1. open eclipse ->  help -> install new software -> drop down -> select eclipse (off url) 

-> WEB XML section -> check checkmark -> install only JAVA EE (servelet)

automatially after installation -> eclipse will restart 

2. open eclipse -> help -> eclipse marketplace -> JAVA EE 

automatially after installation -> eclipse will restart 


install tomcat server : java compatible server to lanuch web projects 

open browser ->  https://tomcat.apache.org/download-10.cgi 

choose ur OS -> based on the download latest version 


create -> new -> web project -> give name 

create new package : ndv  

under the package -> right click create a sevelet ->  

right click on project -> run on server -> attach server -> browser will open .. 



































